00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:49, 16
Mr. Somers is very well-connected,

139
00:06:49, 16 --> 00:06:52,150
and has friends in the District Attorney's office.

140
00:06:52,150 --> 00:06:53,383
Which is why, if Emily Nocenti

141
00:06:53,383 --> 00:06:55,650
is to get justice for her father's death,

142
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:58,116
if Martin Somers is to get justice for his crimes,

143
00:06:58,116 --> 00:07:01,916
then someone is going to have to do it for them.

144
00:07:13,383 --> 00:07:15,216
Martin Somers.

145
00:07:15,216 --> 00:07:17,116
Laurel's targeted   the worst of Starling City,

146
00:07:17,116 --> 00:07:22,416
so it's no surprise   his name is on   my father's list.

147
00:07:23,350 --> 00:07:26,750
The city's police and   the D.A. can't stop him...

148
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:27,783
or won't.

149
00:07:27,783 --> 00:07:33,116
Laurel thinks she's   the only one willing   to bring him to justice.

150
00:07:33,116 --> 00:07:36, 50
She's wrong.

151
00:07:38,683 --> 00:07:39,750
You, listen up.

152
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:42,816
The longer this goes on, the more likely the media is gonna crucify me.

153
00:07:42,816 --> 00:07:45,516
You shut this trial down, do you understand me?

154
00:07:45,516 --> 00:07:47,550
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

155
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,250
(MEN GROANING)

156
00:07:49,550 --> 00:07:51,416
What the hell?

157
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:56,150
(THUDDING)

158
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:58,150
(CHOKING)

159
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03, 50
Martin Somers... Who the hell are you?

160
00:08:03, 50 --> 00:08:04,316
...you've failed this city.

161
00:08:04,316 --> 00:08:06,483
SOMERS: No! No, no, no, no, no!

162
00:08:06,716 --> 00:08:08,216
You're gonna testify in that trial.

163
00:08:08,216 --> 00:08:12,216
