199
00:10:20,675 --> 00:10:21,508
Where you going?

200
00:10:21,508 --> 00:10:24,608
Uh... Somewhere loud and smoky.

201
00:10:24,908 --> 00:10:27,442
And don't bother trying to pickpocket my stash this time,

202
00:10:27,442 --> 00:10:30,408
because I'm gonna go get drunk instead.

203
00:10:31,108 --> 00:10:32,642
Thea,

204
00:10:33,  8 --> 00:10:37, 75
do you think this is what Dad would want for you?

205
00:10:37,442 --> 00:10:39,942
Dead people don't want anything.

206
00:10:39,942 --> 00:10:41,975
It's one of the benefits of being dead.

207
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,808
I was dead.

208
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:46,  8
And I wanted a lot.

209
00:10:46,  8 --> 00:10:48,475
Except for your family.

210
00:10:48,842 --> 00:10:50,342
You've been home a week and all you do

211
00:10:50,342 --> 00:10:55,  8
is avoid Mom, ignore Walter, and judge me.

212
00:10:55,  8 --> 00:10:56,808
(SIGHING)

213
00:10:56,808 --> 00:10:58,475
Don't wait up.

214
00:11:02,442 --> 00:11:05,508
Well, I owe you an apology, Mr. Somers.

215
00:11:05,508 --> 00:11:07,142
We come all the way down to your docks,

216
00:11:07,142 --> 00:11:10,175
and it turns out, you don't need the police after all.

217
00:11:10,175 --> 00:11:11,775
Which is exactly what I've been saying.

218
00:11:11,775 --> 00:11:14,408
Yeah. So I guess that 9-1-1 call we got last night

219
00:11:14,408 --> 00:11:16,675
from your stevedore, saying that you were getting attacked

220
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:18,842
by a guy in a green hood and a bow and arrow...

221
00:11:18,842 --> 00:11:24, 42
I guess... Well, was that a practical joke?

222
00:11:26,308 --> 00:11:28, 42
These guys like to fool around.

223
00:11:28, 42 --> 00:11:29,675
QUENTIN: Yeah.

