00:13:15,942 --> 00:13:18,642
is a result of its targeted diversification.

255
00:13:18,642 --> 00:13:22,675
We have been making impressive inroads in cutting-edge fields

256
00:13:22,675 --> 00:13:25, 75
like bio-tech and clean energy.

257
00:13:25, 75 --> 00:13:26,342
OLIVER: That's neat. Excuse me?

258
00:13:26,342 --> 00:13:30,708
Can I get a sparkling water, or something cold, please?

259
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:31,908
Sweetheart, Oliver,

260
00:13:31,908 --> 00:13:34,175
Walter and I have something to discuss with you.

261
00:13:34,175 --> 00:13:35,275
Come, please sit.

262
00:13:35,275 --> 00:13:38,742
Mom, it makes me nervous when you ask me to sit down.

263
00:13:39,542 --> 00:13:41,908
The company's about to break ground on a new site

264
00:13:41,908 --> 00:13:43,608
for the Applied Sciences division,

265
00:13:43,608 --> 00:13:45,708
and we would like to honor your father

266
00:13:45,708 --> 00:13:48,142
by dedicating the building in his name. Nice.

267
00:13:48,142 --> 00:13:52,142
And we'd like to make an announcement at the dedication

268
00:13:52,142 --> 00:13:55,775
that you will be taking a leadership position in the company.

269
00:13:55,775 --> 00:13:58,208
No. No, your... Your company.

270
00:13:58,208 --> 00:13:59,675
No, I don't want to lead anything.

271
00:13:59,675 --> 00:14:02,908
Besides, Walter is doing a very good job here.

272
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:07,408
MOIRA: You said that you wanted to be a different person.

273
00:14:07,708 --> 00:14:09,975
And you are Robert Queen's son.

274
00:14:09,975 --> 00:14:11,442
I don't need to be reminded of that.

275
00:14:11,442 --> 00:14:13,642
Well, obviously you do.

276
00:14:16,975 --> 00:14:22,742
Everyone here understands that this transition is really difficult for you.

277
00:14:22,742 --> 00:14:24,742
Thank you, Walter.

278
00:14:25,842 --> 00:14:26,808
Which part, though?

279
00:14:26,808 --> 00:14:30,108
Everyone fantasizing that I got my MBA while I was on the island?

280
00:14:30,108 --> 00:14:35,342
Or the fact that my father's CFO now sleeps down the hall from me?

281
00:14:42,908 --> 00:14:48,908
You know, five years ago, your irresponsibility was somewhat charming.

282
00:14:50,608 --> 00:14:52,875
It is a lot less so now.

283
00:15:05,142 --> 00:15:08,275
REPORTER: There he is! (CAMERAS CLICKING)

284
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:11,808
(PRESS CLAMORING)

285
00:15:19,608 --> 00:15:22,275
The driver will be here in a minute.

286
00:15:24,  8 --> 00:15:25,242
Okay.

287
00:15:25,242 --> 00:15:28,542
You know, I spent the first 27 years of my life in Starling City,

288
00:15:28,542 --> 00:15:29,842
and the next five in Afghanistan.

289
00:15:29,842 --> 00:15:32,275
You want to know what I learned?

290
00:15:32,675 --> 00:15:35,275
There's no place like home?

291
00:15:35,908 --> 00:15:37,808
No, just the opposite.

292
00:15:38, 75 --> 00:15:39,908
Home is a battlefield.

293
00:15:39,908 --> 00:15:42,675
Back home, they're all trying to get you.

294
00:15:42,675 --> 00:15:47,808
Get you to open up, be somebody you're not sure you are anymore.

295
00:15:50,542 --> 00:15:51,542
Or I could be wrong.

296
00:15:51,542 --> 00:15:52,808
Maybe after five years alone,

297
00:15:52,808 --> 00:15:57,275
you're not as messed up in the head as you have every right to be.

298
00:16:02,142 --> 00:16:04,342
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

299
00:16:05, 75 --> 00:16:06,575
Hey!

300
00:16:06,575 --> 00:16:08,508
Hey, get away!

301
00:16:10,442 --> 00:16:11,875
Hey!

302
00:16:15,342 --> 00:16:17,  8
(COUGHING)

303
00:16:17,708 --> 00:16:19,175
Dad?

304
00:16:30, 75 --> 00:16:31,875
(RETCHING)

305
00:16:34,142 --> 00:16:35,375
(SEAGULLS GET LOUDER)

306
00:16:35,375 --> 00:16:38,875
Hey! Hey, stay away from him!

307
00:16:40,508 --> 00:16:42,508
(COUGHING)

308
00:17:00,342 --> 00:17:02,442
(GRUNTING)

309
00:17:12, 75 --> 00:17:13,975
Well, we anticipate   that Somers' attorney

310
00:17:13,975 --> 00:17:19,942
will try and paint you as blinded by grief or looking to make a buck.

311
00:17:20,742 --> 00:17:21,942
This isn't about the money.

312
00:17:21,942 --> 00:17:23,242
I just want justice for my father.

313
00:17:23,242 --> 00:17:28, 42
Emily, there are a lot of people who don't want this trial to proceed.

314
00:17:28, 42 --> 00:17:28,908
Dangerous people.

315
00:17:28,908 --> 00:17:30,242
My mother died when I was a baby,

316
00:17:30,242 --> 00:17:33,242
and my father has been the only family I've ever known

317
00:17:33,242 --> 00:17:35,375
and they slit his throat.

318
00:17:36,942 --> 00:17:38,475
They are going to have to kill me

319
00:17:38,475 --> 00:17:39,808
if they want me to give this up.

320
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:42,242
Well let's hope it doesn't come to that.

321
00:17:42,242 --> 00:17:44,375
QUENTIN: And it won't.

322
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,242
What's going on?

323
00:17:46,242 --> 00:17:47,642
What's going on is that the three of you

324
00:17:47,642 --> 00:17:49,242
are getting around-the-clock police protection. Okay?

325
00:17:49,242 --> 00:17:50,375
Get used to their faces,

326
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:52,408
because they're going with you everywhere you go, no arguments.

327
00:17:52,408 --> 00:17:53,842
I'm a lawyer. I live to argue.

328
00:17:53,842 --> 00:17:56,942
I'm your father. I live to keep you safe.

329
00:17:57,608 --> 00:17:59,542
Um, Emily, let's go grab a cup of coffee, okay?

330
00:17:59,542 --> 00:18:03,442
Yes, why not do that? Thank you. Please, go with them.

331
00:18:03,442 --> 00:18:05,108
Stay there.

332
00:18:06,308 --> 00:18:07,442
Protective custody?

333
00:18:07,442 --> 00:18:10,742
I seem to recall you trying that once I discovered boys also.

334
00:18:10,742 --> 00:18:12,275
Didn't work then either. (SIGHING)

335
00:18:12,275 --> 00:18:14,208
This isn't a joke, Laurel.

336
00:18:14,208 --> 00:18:17,  8
Martin Somers got attacked last night.

337
00:18:17,842 --> 00:18:18,842
What? Yeah.

338
00:18:18,842 --> 00:18:20,208
By who? It doesn't matter.

339
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:22,742
Point is, you have whipped up a storm with these guys,

340
00:18:22,742 --> 00:18:26,575
and until the dust settles you'll be protected, okay?

341
00:18:26,575 --> 00:18:28,242
End of discussion.

342
00:18:28,242 --> 00:18:30,542
That might have worked when I was eight.

343
00:18:30,542 --> 00:18:31,875
But it's not gonna work anymore.

344
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:33, 42
End of discussion, Laurel!

345
00:18:33, 42 --> 00:18:34,942
You're insistent on doing your job, that's great.

346
00:18:34,942 --> 00:18:36,142
But this is me doing mine, okay?

347
00:18:36,142 --> 00:18:37,642
And not just as a father, but as a cop.

348
00:18:37,642 --> 00:18:41,775
These people, they are more dangerous than you are willing to admit.

349
00:18:41,775 --> 00:18:44,475
And you've made them angry.

350
00:18:51,775 --> 00:18:54,742
Thank you for coming. Anything for a friend.

351
00:18:54,742 --> 00:18:55,908
We're not friends.

352
00:18:55,908 --> 00:18:58,208
You smuggle drugs, I let you use my port.

353
00:18:58,208 --> 00:18:59,908
For which you're paid a lot of money.

354
00:18:59,908 --> 00:19:02,608
I don't get paid enough to have arrows shot at me.

355
00:19:02,608 --> 00:19:04,442
You need to take this guy seriously.

356
00:19:04,442 --> 00:19:07,108
He is a bigger threat to your operation than Nocenti ever was.

357
00:19:07,108 --> 00:19:09,608
Except now it's Nocenti's daughter who's the problem.

358
00:19:09,608 --> 00:19:13, 75
Unlike your friend with the hood, we know where to find her.

359
00:19:13, 75 --> 00:19:14,108
Don't be an idiot.

360
00:19:14,108 --> 00:19:16,975
You take out Emily Nocenti, and Laurel Lance will never let this go.

361
00:19:16,975 --> 00:19:18,508
She won't stop until she burns you,

362
00:19:18,508 --> 00:19:22, 75
me, and then the entire Triad to the ground.

363
00:19:22,308 --> 00:19:24,875
Then we kill Miss Lance.

364
00:19:30,542 --> 00:19:32,375
Attorney for   shipping magnate,   Martin Somers,

365
00:19:32,375 --> 00:19:35,108
has confirmed his client   has no intention   of testifying,

366
00:19:35,108 --> 00:19:38,608
maintaining his innocence   in the wrongful death   of Victor Nocenti.

367
00:19:38,608 --> 00:19:40,542
Nocenti's body   was found   four weeks ago.

368
00:19:40,542 --> 00:19:43,842
We'll keep you updated   as more information   becomes available.

369
00:19:43,842 --> 00:19:45,408
Wait, how did you get those?

370
00:19:45,408 --> 00:19:46,742
(SIGHING) Don't you knock?

371
00:19:46,742 --> 00:19:50,208
No, wait... Mom said that there were scars, but...

372
00:19:55,208 --> 00:20:00, 75
I'm... Oliver, what happened to you out there?

373
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:07, 75
I don't want to talk about it.

374
00:20:07,575 --> 00:20:09,142
(SCOFFS)

375
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:11,342
Of course you don't.

376
00:20:11,342 --> 00:20:14,  8
You never want to talk to me about anything.

377
00:20:14,  8 --> 00:20:16,508
Except for my social life. Wait!

378
00:20:17,375 --> 00:20:19,275
Where are you going?

379
00:20:19,275 --> 00:20:21,308
Why should I tell you?

380
00:20:23,808 --> 00:20:25,742
I'm sorry, Thea.

381
00:20:26,508 --> 00:20:32, 75
I need to get better at talking about what happened to me there.

382
00:20:35,275 --> 00:20:37,608
But I'm not ready yet.

383
00:20:37,608 --> 00:20:39, 75
Okay?

384
00:20:41,242 --> 00:20:43,175
Do you have a second?

385
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:45,408
Yeah.

386
00:20:46,275 --> 00:20:47,942
Good.

387
00:20:47,942 --> 00:20:50,675
I wanna show you something out back.

388
00:20:53,175 --> 00:20:57,208
Sometimes, when I felt... Whatever...

389
00:20:57,475 --> 00:20:59,808
I'd come here.

390
00:21:02,708 --> 00:21:07,142
About a month after the funerals, Mom stopped going out.

391
00:21:07,775 --> 00:21:11,142
Pretty soon, she stopped talking altogether.

392
00:21:11,942 --> 00:21:16, 42
The house got so quiet, so I'd come here.

393
00:21:17,508 --> 00:21:19,375
To talk to you.

394
00:21:22,408 --> 00:21:23,542
I mean, stupid stuff.

395
00:21:23,542 --> 00:21:28,175
Like what I was doing that day, what boy I had a crush on...

396
00:21:28,175 --> 00:21:31,  8
And then sometimes, I'd ask you,

397
00:21:31,  8 --> 00:21:35,142
beg you, to find your way home to me.

398
00:21:35,475 --> 00:21:36,942
Now, here you are.

399
00:21:36,942 --> 00:21:42, 75
And the truth is, I felt closer to you when you were dead.

400
00:21:43, 42 --> 00:21:46,342
Look, I know it was hell where you were.

401
00:21:46,342 --> 00:21:48,942
But it was hell here too.

402
00:21:51,242 --> 00:21:53,742
You gotta let me in, Ollie.

403
00:21:55,242 --> 00:21:57,942
You gotta let someone in.

404
00:22:12,342 --> 00:22:14,342
(DOORBELL RINGING)

405
00:22:30,208 --> 00:22:31,275
Hi.

406
00:22:31,275 --> 00:22:33, 42
Are you okay?

407
00:22:33,242 --> 00:22:34,375
There are two cop cars outside.

408
00:22:34,375 --> 00:22:36,275
How am I supposed to stay away from you

409
00:22:36,275 --> 00:22:38,975
if you won't stay away from me?

410
00:22:39,442 --> 00:22:42,208
I... What are you doing here, Ollie?

411
00:22:42,808 --> 00:22:43,942
My sister took...

412
00:22:43,942 --> 00:22:49,208
She pointed out to me that I have been distant since I got back and that...

413
00:22:49,442 --> 00:22:52,542
It would probably be a good idea if I let somebody in.

414
00:22:52,542 --> 00:22:56,342
So, you thought you'd start with the first person you pushed away.

415
00:22:56,342 --> 00:22:58,775
I did that to protect you.

416
00:22:59, 42 --> 00:23:00,275
And then I saw you yesterday,

417
00:23:00,275 --> 00:23:02,908
and I realized that I hurt you.

418
00:23:04, 75 --> 00:23:05,708
(SIGHING)

419
00:23:11,508 --> 00:23:13, 75
Thank you.

420
00:23:16,775 --> 00:23:17,908
Wow.

421
00:23:17,908 --> 00:23:21,375
This place hasn't changed in five years. (CHUCKLING)

422
00:23:21,375 --> 00:23:25,542
I haven't really had time to redecorate.

423
00:23:26,208 --> 00:23:28, 42
I'm a jerk.

424
00:23:28,308 --> 00:23:32,775
Before the island, I was a jerk, and now I'm just a...

425
00:23:34,475 --> 00:23:36,175
I'm a damaged jerk.

426
00:23:36,175 --> 00:23:38,175
What's in the bag?

427
00:23:39,142 --> 00:23:41,608
I thought about many things on the island,

428
00:23:41,608 --> 00:23:43,842
but there was one thing that I thought about every day.

429
00:23:43,842 --> 00:23:44,975
I actually dreamed about it,

430
00:23:44,975 --> 00:23:48,275
and I promised myself that if I ever got a chance

431
00:23:48,275 --> 00:23:52,408
to do it again, I'd do it with you.

432
00:23:56,308 --> 00:23:58, 75
Eat ice cream.

433
00:24:03,408 --> 00:24:06,108
This is as good as I remember.

434
00:24:09,275 --> 00:24:11,975
My mother wants me to join the company.

435
00:24:11,975 --> 00:24:14,842
Yeah. Take my rightful place.

436
00:24:14,842 --> 00:24:20,442
I can't exactly picture you as master of the universe.

437
00:24:23,408 --> 00:24:26,342
You know, after five years,

438
00:24:27,308 --> 00:24:29,308
I have plans.

439
00:24:29,842 --> 00:24:32,408
I have things that I have to do.

440
00:24:32,408 --> 00:24:35,  8
I can't do that if I'm...

441
00:24:36,308 --> 00:24:37,342
I don't know...

442
00:24:37,342 --> 00:24:41,308
Attending board meetings and stockholder briefings.

443
00:24:42,642 --> 00:24:44,375
Oliver? Hmm?

444
00:24:44,375 --> 00:24:46,342
You're an adult.

445
00:24:46,708 --> 00:24:47,908
You can say no.

446
00:24:47,908 --> 00:24:49,442
Oh, I tried.

447
00:24:49,908 --> 00:24:51,675
Didn't take.

448
00:24:51,675 --> 00:24:54,608
Well, then don't tell her.

449
00:24:54,808 --> 00:24:56, 75
Show her.

450
00:24:56, 75 --> 00:25:00,342
Be the person that you want her to see you as.

451
00:25:01,542 --> 00:25:03,242
Trust me.

452
00:25:03,708 --> 00:25:06,808
I have plenty of experience with disapproving parents.

453
00:25:06,808 --> 00:25:11, 42
I have been on the receiving end of your father's disapproval.

454
00:25:11,942 --> 00:25:13,908
He blames himself more than he blames you.

455
00:25:13,908 --> 00:25:18, 42
He thinks that, you know, maybe if he and Sarah were closer,

456
00:25:18, 42 --> 00:25:21, 75
she would have told him about the boat trip.

457
00:25:21, 75 --> 00:25:24,908
And he could have stopped her from going with you.

458
00:25:25,108 --> 00:25:26,408
I am sorry.

459
00:25:26,408 --> 00:25:28,575
You apologized already.

460
00:25:30,742 --> 00:25:33,375
And it'll never be enough.

461
00:25:35,575 --> 00:25:38,308
(THUD) Did you hear that?

462
00:25:39,342 --> 00:25:40,742
What?

463
00:25:41,242 --> 00:25:43,142
(SOFT FOOTSTEP)

464
00:25:45,308 --> 00:25:47,508
There's someone on the fire escape.

465
00:25:49,542 --> 00:25:51,542
Hey, come on.. What are...

466
00:25:56,308 --> 00:25:58,208
(MACHINE GUN FIRING)

467
00:26:00,408 --> 00:26:02,142
(LAUREL SCREAMS)

468
00:26:02,775 --> 00:26:04,475
(GUNFIRE CONTINUING)

469
00:26:08,  8 --> 00:26:09,608
(GUNSHOTS)

470
00:26:12,842 --> 00:26:15,475
(BOTH GRUNTING)

471
00:26:30,875 --> 00:26:31,742
Are you hurt? No.

472
00:26:31,742 --> 00:26:33,575
Are you hurt, Mr. Queen? No! No.

473
00:26:33,575 --> 00:26:37,408
This is why it's a good idea to have a bodyguard.

474
00:26:39,208 --> 00:26:40,875
(SOFTLY) You okay?

475
00:26:44,742 --> 00:26:46,575
(SIREN WAILING)

476
00:26:51,875 --> 00:26:53,942
Daddy! Oh, thank God.

477
00:26:53,942 --> 00:26:57, 75
Thank God. Are you all right? I'm okay.

478
00:26:57,508 --> 00:26:59,342
Those cops that you put on me...

479
00:26:59,342 --> 00:27:00,942
(SIGHING)

480
00:27:00,942 --> 00:27:01,842
They...

481
00:27:01,842 --> 00:27:05,608
I went outside to ask for a light and they were both dead in the squad car.

482
00:27:09,475 --> 00:27:11,875
Mr. Diggle, thank you.

483
00:27:11,875 --> 00:27:14,642
Feel free to run as many red lights in the city as you want.

484
00:27:14,642 --> 00:27:15,875
I was just doing my job, sir.

485
00:27:15,875 --> 00:27:18,608
No, your job is protecting him.

486
00:27:19,108 --> 00:27:23,675
It seems like whenever you're with one of my daughters, people die.

487
00:27:23,675 --> 00:27:25,408
You stay away from Laurel,

488
00:27:25,408 --> 00:27:27,242
or I swear the next time you disappear,

489
00:27:27,242 --> 00:27:28,608
it will be permanent. Dad!

490
00:27:28,608 --> 00:27:30,575
No, Laurel... It's okay.

491
00:27:30,575 --> 00:27:32,342
I understand.

492
00:27:34,  8 --> 00:27:35,508
Yeah.

493
00:27:41,342 --> 00:27:42,242
Here!

494
00:27:42,242 --> 00:27:44,342
I'd say thank you, but I don't think that would cover it.

495
00:27:44,342 --> 00:27:47,  8
Well, like I told your cop friend, I was just doing my job.

496
00:27:47,  8 --> 00:27:50,542
Besides, I think it should be you that I'm thanking.

497
00:27:54,775 --> 00:27:56,608
What for? The knife.

498
00:27:57,442 --> 00:27:58,375
The knife.

499
00:27:58,375 --> 00:28:00,408
I got lucky. That was a kitchen knife.

500
00:28:00,408 --> 00:28:01,708
It wasn't even weighted properly,

501
00:28:01,708 --> 00:28:04,108
yet you threw it with accuracy across a 10-foot room.

502
00:28:04,108 --> 00:28:05,342
Exactly. I got lucky.

503
00:28:05,342 --> 00:28:09,942
I'm not the kind of man you want to take for a fool, Mr. Queen, you understand me?

504
00:28:10,175 --> 00:28:10,975
Yes.

505
00:28:10,975 --> 00:28:14,642
And I think I'm just beginning to understand the kind of man you are.

506
00:28:14,642 --> 00:28:16,975
Shouldn't take you very long.

507
00:28:16,975 --> 00:28:18,342
I'm shallow.

508
00:28:18,342 --> 00:28:21,  8
And very tired, so...

509
00:28:23,675 --> 00:28:25,208
Good night.

510
00:28:27,442 --> 00:28:28,308
Good night, sir.

511
00:28:28,308 --> 00:28:30,308
OLIVER:   It wasn't how   I wanted things to go.

512
00:28:30,308 --> 00:28:33,708
I wanted to give   Martin Somers   the chance to confess

513
00:28:33,708 --> 00:28:35,275
and face a court's justice,

514
00:28:35,275 --> 00:28:39,675
but he chose to go   after someone   I care about instead.

515
00:28:39,675 --> 00:28:43,108
